fields.description:
It is located in the Gràcia neighborhood (Barcelona).

Actually, it's not a cafeteria, it's a restaurant, but outside of peak lunch or dinner hours, you can go to work without problems. 

It has an interior part and an exterior part. The patio is full of plants and this piece of nature within the city is very pleasant. 

The coffee is ok.
fields.address: Carrer de Minerva, 2, Gràcia, 08006 Barcelona
fields.name: Les Filles Cafè

fields.description:
The place is very impressive due to its structure, the top floor has a very nice view of the surrounding campus.

The exhibition of original plans and drawings, although not very large, is interesting.

It is a good space to study, since it has many areas in addition to Internet and electricity connections.
fields.address: 9500 Gilman Dr, La Jolla, CA 92093, Estados Unidos
fields.name: Geisel Library

fields.description:
Located in the Raval neighborhood, Bar Central is located in a green garden like a beautiful patio, full of plants and in an environment that inspires you to be creative. It is inside the La Central bookstore. And it was inaugurated on Sant Jordi (a very beautiful and important holiday for Catalonia. Its peculiar Book Day). 
Located next to the space formerly occupied by the 'Capella de la Misericòrdia' and with a surface area of ​​850 m².
fields.address: Carrer d'Elisabets, 6, Ciutat Vella, 08001 Barcelona
fields.name: La Central del Raval

fields.description:
La Casa Encendida is social and cultural center located in the Lavapiés neighbourhood. 

The center has a library, youth library, media library and office room, as well as a cafeteria. The Terrace of La Casa Encendida is an extraordinary place that houses a wide variety of plant species and allows you to contemplate the best sunsets in the city. It is home to the Terrace coffee bar, open all year round, with exquisite breakfasts, brunches, and an extensive list of wines, cocktails and beers.

It is located in a neo-Mudejar style building that has a monumental character, designed by the architect Fernando Arbós and inaugurated in 1913.

Coffee Shop is located in floor 1 and terrace coffee bar in floor 0.
fields.address: Rda. de Valencia, 2, Centro, 28012 Madrid
fields.name: La Casa Encendida

fields.description:
Their coffee is excellent. It's from different places of the world and you can smell it before you taste it. For example, americano's price is 130 baths (3,3€). 

They don't have wifi. You can go here to write, read or enjoy your journey.
fields.address: 24, 2 Ari 4 Alley, Samsen Nai, Phaya Thai, Bangkok 10400, Tailandia
fields.name: NANA Coffee Roasters Ari

fields.description:
It is located in Vught (Nederland). 

After an extensive renovation the church, which dates from 1884, was redeveloped into a multifunctional center containing a library and a museum but also a bar and shops, in 2018.

A nice cozy café in the heart of a big library. If you go to the second floor, you may enjoy the pictorial architecture. 

The place is full of historical information from WW2.
fields.address: Heuvel 2, 5261 EE Vught, Países Bajos
fields.name: Petrus Library

fields.description: The library houses a reading area, a meditation space, activity room, a drinking bar and a resting area
fields.address: M848+FQ7, Changli County, Qinhuangdao, Hebei, China, 316939
fields.name: Seashore Library

fields.description:
Norai Raval is the restaurant of Museu Marítim de Barcelona located in the Ciutat Vella neighbourhood. 

By enjoying the Norai restaurant you will also be contributing to the Norai project, a social and training project that every year allows access to the labor market for people from the Raval neighborhood in vulnerable situations.

It is a very bright space thanks to its large window that overlooks the port and it’s big and open concept.
fields.address: Av. de les Drassanes, 1, Ciutat Vella, 08001 Barcelona
fields.name: Norai Raval

fields.description:
It is located in the Suthep area of ​​Chiang Mai.

Because it is in the CMU University grounds, it's a good place to work or study. 

It is nice to sit outside, too. This is a space full of greenery, where you can enjoy the scenery of nature while drinking coffee.
fields.address: คณะเกษตรศาสตร์ มหาวิทยาลัยเชียงใหม่ 239 Suthep Rd, Tambon Su Thep, Mueang Chiang Mai District, Chiang Mai 50200, Tailandia
fields.name: Blue coffee at Agriculture CMU

fields.description:
Piccolo Vicolo is a coffee shop that forms part of Galile Oasis, an arts and community hub and boutique hotel in the regenerated Ratchathewi neighborhood, which also houses a gallery and theatre. It is tucked down Wat Phraya Yang alley, hence the name, which translates from Italian to ‘small alley’. 

The open space is filled with verdant plants and vintage furniture for a laidback, laptop-friendly setting, where freelancers will feel right at home.

They have plugs, good wifi and good coffee for good price (100 baths for Americano).
fields.address: 535 31 ตรอก Wat Phraya Yang Alley, Khwaeng Thanon Phetchaburi, Ratchathewi, Bangkok 10400
fields.name: Piccolo Vicolo Café

fields.description:
Helsinki Central Library Oodi is a living meeting place at Kansalaistori square, right at the heart of Helsinki.

Oodi is a non-commercial, urban public space that is open to all, right opposite the Parliament Building.

It provides its users with knowledge, new skills and stories, and is an easy place to access for learning, story immersion, work and relaxation. It is a library of a new era, a living and functional meeting place open for all.

This library has a different spaces: Children story room, workspace, work desks, seating spaces, studios and game room.
fields.address: Töölönlahdenkatu 4, 00100 Helsinki, Finlandia
fields.name: Oodi Library

fields.description:
It is located in the center of the University of Chicago Campus.

It is surrounded by a variety of different buildings.
fields.address: 1100 E 57th St, Chicago, IL 60637, Estados Unidos
fields.name: Joe & Rika Mansueto Library

fields.description:
This is the typical place we wouldn't go to work. In our case we went to read and write, and it was very calm.

The tea is very good, and the atmosphere is very relaxing. You can pour yourself water, they refill your tea when you finish it and you can spend a few hours there enjoying the atmosphere.

The place is beautiful and worth it.
fields.address: No. 174, Section 1, Zhonghua Rd, Wanhua District, Taipei City, Taiwán 108
fields.name: Eighty-Eightea Rinbansyo

fields.description:
It is located in Santiago de Compostela, Galicia. In the north of Spain.

It was designed by the American architect Peter Eisenman and forms, together with six other buildings, the City of Culture of Galicia.

Its shapes simulate the geology of the area.

Keep in mind that it doesn't have many outlets due to its architecture.
fields.address: Cidade da Cultura, Avenida manual Fraga Iribarne, s/n, 15707 Santiago de Compostela, A Coruña
fields.name: Biblioteca y Archivo de Galicia

fields.description:
It's located in the Old Town of Bangkok.

It is a quiet, picturesque space with white walls and good coffee. They have a small terrace where you can read or enjoy a drink, which directly overlooks the canal.

JEDI is a mutual ground for all thinkers run by creative individuals with high complexity through fresh robust brewery, arts, food and spirits, located in the heart of Bangkok.

They often have exhibitions and artworks or paintings by artists.
fields.address: 10 Boripat Rd, Ban Bat, Pom Prap Sattru Phai, Bangkok 10100
fields.name: JEDI Café & Bar

fields.description:
It's located in the old town of Bangkok, specifically inside the Doble B Hostel.

This café is made of concrete and wood. Finding spaces with natural light in the old town is not easy due to its architecture, so they built it in such a way that it allows natural light to enter. A modern building that invites people to hang out in an open-air space in a four and a half-story shophouse.

I was quite surprised to find a place where I could spend the whole day working and sipping coffee without feeling hot because of the cool breeze that blows all day except during the very hot part of the day when there is a lot of natural light, the seating area in the center of the café can be a bit hot. The interior designer has designed a small room for those who don’t like Open Air spaces or during hot times.

Bite & Bond is open from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. on Tuesdays through Sundays for individuals looking for a cup of coffee and pastries.
fields.address: 35 Trok Nawa, Sao Chingcha, Phra Nakhon, Bangkok 10200, Tailandia
fields.name: Bit and Bond

fields.description:
It is located 

Designed by Rem Koolhaas, the diamond shaped exterior of the library belies its spacious interior, which prioritizes light and visibility. 

The bookshelves themselves are an integral part of the building, rising out of the floor and blending into the architecture; Innovative technologies are seamlessly integrated throughout the building, enhancing accessibility and efficiency.

There are more than 1 million books. It is a very quiet and clean place.
fields.name: Qatar National Library

fields.description:
To use this library you have to pay. The price is 50 Taiwan dollars. In euros about €1.40 and in dollars $1.55. Which isn't much but it keeps it from being full.

They force you to take off your shoes. You have a small interior garden where you can go out and get some fresh air. The internet is good and being specialized in design you have thousands of magazines and books on the subject.

Sometimes they do events inside, but otherwise it's very quiet.
fields.address: No. 133號, Guangfu S Rd, Xinyi District, Taipei City, Taiwán 110
fields.name: Not Just Library

fields.description:
A library in the center of New York, with plugs, internet and without paying admission.

What more could you want.
fields.address: 18 W 53rd St, New York, NY 10019, Estados Unidos
fields.name: 53rd Street Library

fields.description:
This is a library for an art university located in the suburbs of Tokyo. 

Passing through the main entrance gate, the site lies behind a front garden with small and large trees, and stretches up a gentle slope.
fields.address: 2 Chome-1723 Yarimizu, Hachioji, Tokyo 192-0375, Japón
fields.name: Tama Art University Library

fields.description:
Bukhan Mountain, better known as Bukhansan, has one of the best hiking trails in Seoul. Every year, countless tourists and locals visit the mountain for a challenging hike. Cafe Sanare is located at the foot of Bukhansan, and its serenity makes it a great spot to unwind after a long day of hiking.

The interior of the cafe is furnished in a mid-century modern style, with rattan furniture, neutral-coloured cushions, and metal tables with transparent glass tops.
fields.address: 56 Samyang-ro 181-gil, Gangbuk-gu, Seoul, Corea del Sur
fields.name: Cafe Sanare

fields.description: It is located on the second floor of the East Wing of Lone Mountain. Free Wi-Fi, ample plugs, quiet, and dark academia vibes.
fields.address: 2130 Fulton St, San Francisco, CA 94117, Estados Unidos
fields.name: Del Santo Reading Room

fields.description:
The Suwon Starfield Library is located in the Suwon Starfield Mall which is located just outside Hwaseo Station on the no. 1 line just outside of Seoul. 

Covering an area of over 2,800 square meters, it houses more than 70,000 books and over 600 magazines. There are two levels of seating areas to choose from at your convenience.
fields.address: Corea del Sur, Seoul, Gangnam District, Yeongdong-daero, 513 스타필드 코엑스몰 B1
fields.name: Starfield Library

fields.description:
This library is spacious and well-appointed, featuring cozy areas with sofas where you can relax and read, as well as comfortable tables for studying. The only downside is that it doesn't have Wi-Fi.

What we appreciate the most is the library's architecture. The design of the staircases and the distribution of the books are particularly fascinating.

We recommend visiting the library alone, either to read or simply to appreciate the architecture. While it may not be ideal for working due to the lack of internet, it's definitely worth a visit if you enjoy architectural beauty or want a peaceful place to read.
fields.address: Eje 1 Nte. S/N, Buenavista, Cuauhtémoc, 06350 Ciudad de México, CDMX, México
fields.name: Biblioteca Vasconcelos

fields.description:
It is located in the Ciutat Vella neighborhood. This cafeteria is located in the Convent of San Agustín, a Gothic building from the 14th century, and has a terrace overlooking the cloister that transmits tranquility and meditation. 
On Thursday and Friday afternoons they play live music, and it is a highly recommended place. It is a very nice and quiet place away from the hustle and bustle of the city.
fields.address: C/ del Comerç, 36, Ciutat Vella, 08003 Barcelona
fields.name: Convento de San Agustín

fields.description: Kabuki is a very special place. It specializes in chocolate and is a very quiet place to go and read.
fields.address: 1 Chome-12-12 Misuji, Taito City, Tokyo 111-0055, Japón
fields.name: Kabuki

fields.description:
It is located in the cultural center of the Binhai district in Tianjin, a coastal metropolis on the outskirts of Beijing, China, facing Ziyun Park.

An oval opening punched through the building is propped open by the Eye, a luminous sphere with an auditorium, which takes the main stage within the atrium and enlarges the perception of space within. Terraced bookshelves which echo the form of the sphere create an interior, topographical, landscape whose contours reach out and wrap around the façade. In this way, the stepped bookshelves within are represented on the outside with each level doubling up as a louvre.

The futuristic library sits within a sheltered gallery, topped with cathedral-like vaulted arches, which wind their way through the scheme.
fields.address: China, Tianjin, Binhai, 旭升路347號
fields.name: Tianjin Binhai Library

fields.description:
It is located in the Asok neighborhood of Bangkok. 

It is an incredible space. It seems like you are inside a laboratory. Clean, pristine and minimalist. All in metal and white. It is a small oasis of freshness in the hot city. 
The chairs are not very comfortable if you are on the stools. The wifi is not very fast.

They are some of the best coffee experts there are. They only have a specialty and each type of coffee, designation of origin and grain is used to make a specific type of coffee. 

Its look is also very nice.

There are plugs for charging.
fields.address: 27 Soi Sukhumvit 19, Khlong Toei Nuea, Watthana, Bangkok 10110, Tailandia
fields.name: WWAPortal

fields.description:
It is located in the Poblenou neighborhood. 

It is a clear, spacious space with lots of light. It has large windows, good coffee and delicious lemonades without sugar. 
In addition, it has a small outdoor space as a quiet zone to concentrate. 

The chairs are not very comfortable. They are stools. It has plugs and good wifi.
fields.address: C. de Pujades, 134, Sant Martí, 08005 Barcelona
fields.name: Mono Café

fields.description: Library, restaurant, yoga studio, and storefront for local artisans all-in-one.
fields.address: Av. de Las Fuentes 180 - B, Jardines del Pedregal, Álvaro Obregón, 01900 Ciudad de México, CDMX, México
fields.name: Tetetlán

fields.description:
It is located in the Poblenou neighborhood.

Library, podcasting and working spaces. Also this library has some spaces to read with hammocks and armchairs and others spaces to concentrate. 

💬Why we love? Natural light, the entire building is modern and with wood. So warm!
fields.address: C/ del Treball, 219, Sant Martí, 08020 Barcelona
fields.name: Gabriel García Márquez Library
